The '''Jedi beacon transceiver''' was an encoded subspace receiver beacon carried by members of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], allowing them to receive signals and broadcasts from the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].

Beacon transceivers were small, portable devices with a display screen and communications transceiver. The transceiver picked up broadcasts from the [[Jedi beacon/Legends|Jedi beacon]] on Coruscant or from any [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi's]] personal [[Comlink/Legends|comlink]]. In emergencies, a Jedi would broadcast [[Emergency Code Nine Thirteen/Legends|Emergency Code Nine Thirteen]] to any beacon transceiver in range, calling for immediate assistance. These devices also picked up recall and retreat signals from the Temple, commonly when [[HoloNet/Legends|HoloNet]] channels were compromised.

When [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] was [[Battle of Coruscant/Legends|attacked]] by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous's]] forces, [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] transmitted a recall message to all Jedi transceivers.

During the execution of [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]], having conquered the Jedi Temple, set the Jedi beacon to call all Jedi home - into the ambush awaiting at the Temple. Any surviving Jedi received the priority signal on their transceivers. However, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] managed to infiltrate the Temple after Vader left for the [[Mustafar system/Legends|Mustafar system]]. Kenobi recalibrated the beacon, warning all Jedi to stay away from Imperial Center.

